ZH: 异见者通常会受到政府的监视。
EN: Dissidents are often subjected to government surveillance.

ZH: 这个国家不容许任何异见者存在。
EN: This country does not tolerate any dissidents.

ZH: 异见者经常受到压制和迫害。
EN: Dissidents are often suppressed and persecuted.

ZH: 异见者为自己的信念而战。
EN: Dissidents fight for their beliefs.

ZH: 异见者被认为是政治上的不稳定因素。
EN: Dissidents are seen as politically destabilizing factors.

ZH: 异见者必须面对严格的审查和审判。
EN: Dissidents must undergo rigorous scrutiny and trials.

ZH: 这个组织成员中有一些异见者。
EN: There are some dissidents among the members of this organization.

ZH: 异见者经常被指责为破坏者。
EN: Dissidents are often accused of being troublemakers.

ZH: 这个政府无情地镇压了所谓的异见者。
EN: This government ruthlessly suppresses so-called dissidents.

ZH: 异见者为自己的信念而坚持不懈。
EN: Dissidents persist in their beliefs.

ZH: 异见者的声音往往被压制。
EN: The voices of dissidents are often suppressed.

ZH: 这个国家不容忍异见者的存在。
EN: This country does not tolerate the presence of dissidents.

ZH: 异见者对当政者提出了挑战。
EN: Dissidents challenge the rulers.

ZH: 这个政权对异见者采取了严厉的打击措施。
EN: This regime has taken harsh measures against dissidents.

ZH: 异见者无法自由表达自己的想法。
EN: Dissidents cannot freely express their thoughts.

ZH: 这个团体拘留了一批异见者。
EN: This group has detained a group of dissidents.

ZH: 异见者的言论自由受到了限制。
EN: The freedom of speech of dissidents is restricted.

ZH: 异见者被迫离开了自己的国家。
EN: Dissidents are forced to leave their own country.

ZH: 这个组织欢迎异见者的不同意见。
EN: This organization welcomes the diverse opinions of dissidents.

ZH: 异见者的抗议活动被镇压得毫不留情。
EN: Dissidents' protest activities are ruthlessly suppressed.
